DON BRAND PRODUCTIONS.

02:38.288 --> 02:40.899
AT THE SOUND OF THE TONE,
PLEASE LEAVE US A MESSAGE.

02:41.030 --> 02:42.597
[MAKES BEEPING SOUND]

02:42.727 --> 02:45.948
DOLORES, IT'S ME. DOLORES,
HEY. WHAT DID NBC SAY?

02:46.078 --> 02:47.602
YEAH. THEY PASSED?
WHAT ARE YOU TALK--

02:48.255 --> 02:50.126
CBS SAID IT'S A
RIPOFF? HEY, LOOK.

02:50.257 --> 02:53.216
I HAD DINOSAUR PARK BEFORE
JURASSIC PARK WAS EVEN A BOOK.

02:53.347 --> 02:55.131
ABC SAID WHAT?

02:55.262 --> 02:57.481
WELL, WHAT DO THEY KNOW? THEY
PASSED ON ALL IN THE FAMILY.

03:02.399 --> 03:04.575
-GARNER: HEY, YOU!
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE!

03:07.926 --> 03:09.232
-WHAT?

03:26.641 --> 03:29.557
-HEY! HEY! SOMEBODY
HELP US OUT HERE!

03:31.385 --> 03:35.040
-BOAT FIRE OFF TOWER 11.
IT'S A RESCUE CODE THREE.

03:39.219 --> 03:40.437
-HELP!

03:44.354 --> 03:47.357
HEY, SOMEBODY HELP!

03:52.493 --> 03:54.234
-[SIREN WAILING]

03:57.759 --> 03:59.239
-GARNER: COULD
USE SOME HELP HERE.

03:59.369 --> 04:00.675
-SORRY, WE'RE BUSY.

04:01.415 --> 04:04.026
-HEY!
-[YELLS]

04:06.158 --> 04:07.595
-DOLORES, YOU
WON'T BELIEVE THIS!

04:07.725 --> 04:09.249
I'M SEEING A WHOLE NEW
ACTION-ADVENTURE SCENE

04:09.379 --> 04:11.468
UNFOLDING RIGHT
BEFORE MY VERY EYES.

04:18.387 --> 04:20.390
-[YELLS]

04:22.043 --> 04:24.307
-AH-- UH-- NO MORE DINOSAURS!

04:24.438 --> 04:27.005
YES, LIFEGUARDS!
AND THEY'RE WEARING--

04:27.136 --> 04:29.573
THEY'RE WEARING BATHING
SUITS. LOVELY BATHING SUITS.

04:29.704 --> 04:32.402
AND BEAUTIFUL PEOPLE, AND--
LISTEN, LISTEN.

04:32.968 --> 04:35.275
WE'RE GOING TO
CALL IT RESCUE BAY.

04:35.405 --> 04:36.798
YEAH! THAT'S RIGHT.

04:36.928 --> 04:38.495
COPYRIGHT THAT. GET OUT.
GET IT COPYRIGHTED.

04:38.626 --> 04:40.105
I'LL CALL YA LATER.

04:42.586 --> 04:45.110
OH, DADDY TAKE ME DOWNTOWN!

04:45.241 --> 04:47.330
-[SHOUTING]

05:00.517 --> 05:02.563
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

05:09.091 --> 05:10.397
-LADY: HEY!

05:16.838 --> 05:18.361
-SON, I NEED YOUR KITE.

05:20.624 --> 05:24.019
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

05:28.545 --> 05:30.417
-[GRUNTS]

05:30.547 --> 05:31.461
-OH!

05:35.987 --> 05:37.511
-ALL RIGHT. GET UP.

05:37.641 --> 05:39.034
-AH!

05:39.164 --> 05:40.818
-HELP! HELP!

05:42.385 --> 05:46.128
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

06:00.098 --> 06:01.970
-OOH!

06:03.319 --> 06:06.409
-HELP! HELP! HELP!

06:06.540 --> 06:08.106
-BACK ME UP.

06:16.506 --> 06:17.855
TAKE MY HAND.

06:25.036 --> 06:26.124
-YOU GUYS OKAY?

06:26.255 --> 06:27.952
-YEAH. SEE YOU ON SHORE.

06:28.910 --> 06:30.912
-OKAY, LET'S GO IN.

06:35.525 --> 06:36.787
-THAT WAS GREAT, YOU GUYS.

06:37.658 --> 06:38.615
-WOO!
-[LAUGHS]

06:38.746 --> 06:39.790
-GOOD GOING OUT THERE.

06:39.921 --> 06:41.357
-THANKS. DID YOU GET YOUR MAN?

06:41.488 --> 06:43.054
-YEAH. WRAPPED HIM UP
AND SHIPPED HIM OFF.

06:43.185 --> 06:46.275
-GREAT.
-WHOA, CONGRATULATIONS!
THIS WAS UNBELIEVABLE!

06:46.406 --> 06:48.669
HOLY-- THAT THING YOU DID WITH
THE KITE WAS FANTASTIC!

06:48.799 --> 06:51.019
IT WAS PERFECT COUNTERPOINT
TO THE ACTION IN THE WATER.

06:51.149 --> 06:52.934
AND YOU WERE ABSOLUTELY AMAZING!

06:53.064 --> 06:54.501
-THANK YOU. NOW
EXCUSE US, PLEASE.

06:54.631 --> 06:56.590
WE HAVE TO GET BACK
TO WORK. SEE YOU GUYS.

06:56.720 --> 06:58.156
-LOOK, JUST PRETEND
I'M NOT HERE, OKAY?

06:58.287 --> 06:59.244
HE'S ALIVE.

06:59.375 --> 07:01.203
-I'D RATHER NOT PRETEND.

07:01.333 --> 07:02.770
-HEY, HEY, LISTEN.
JUST A QUICK QUESTION.

07:02.900 --> 07:04.249
UH, YOU EVER THOUGHT

07:04.380 --> 07:06.034
OF PUTTING MONSTER
WHEELS ON THESE TRUCKS?

07:06.687 --> 07:08.166
OH, JUST A THOUGHT.
MONSTER WHEELS.

07:08.297 --> 07:09.690
-LET ME TAKE A WILD GUESS.

07:09.820 --> 07:11.518
YOU'RE IN THE FILM
BUSINESS. A PRODUCER.

07:11.648 --> 07:13.824
-WELL, TELEVISION.
SERIOUS TELEVISION. DON BRAND.

07:13.955 --> 07:17.480
YEAH, I PRODUCE, DIRECT,
WRITE, EVERYTHING.

07:17.611 --> 07:18.481
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO--

07:18.612 --> 07:19.874
-I WOULDN'T.

07:20.004 --> 07:21.223
-AH. CAN I RIDE
ALONG WITH YOU, MAYBE?

07:21.353 --> 07:23.660
-NO.
-I-- HEY, I'VE DONE RIDE-ALONGS

07:23.791 --> 07:25.880
WITH THE LAPD AND
SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT. HEY!

07:27.534 --> 07:29.231
HEY, COME ON!
WOULDN'T YOU RATHER COOPERATE

07:29.361 --> 07:31.581
AND HAVE AN ACCURATE PORTRAYAL
OF LIFEGUARDS IN ACTION?

07:31.712 --> 07:34.323
-COME ON, YOURSELF. YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT TELEVISION.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.543
-WHO DO I HAVE TO TALK
TO TO ARRANGE SOMETHING?

07:36.673 --> 07:39.197
-I DON'T KNOW. THE CHIEF.

07:39.328 --> 07:41.678
-CHIEF. CHIEF.

07:46.596 --> 07:49.860
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

07:49.991 --> 07:51.775
-A SERIES ABOUT LIFEGUARDS.

07:51.906 --> 07:54.212
I CAN'T BELIEVE NO ONE'S
EVER THOUGHT OF THIS BEFORE!

07:54.343 --> 07:57.346
AH! [EXCLAIMS]

08:04.309 --> 08:06.181
YEAH, DON'T FORGET TO GET
SOME OF THESE BEACH HUMMERS

08:10.881 --> 08:14.668
-WHAT IS THAT TV HUSTLER GUY
DOING ON ONE OF OUR TRUCKS?

08:15.930 --> 08:18.106
-IT'S A RIDE-ALONG.
DIVISION APPROVED IT.

08:18.236 --> 08:19.716
-I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

08:20.630 --> 08:22.240
-I SORT OF ADVISED HIM
TO TALK TO THE CHIEF.

08:22.371 --> 08:23.590
-YOU? OH, PERFECT. YOU.

08:23.720 --> 08:24.721
-I JUST WANTED
TO GET RID OF HIM.

08:26.027 --> 08:27.942
-IF THIS GUY GETS IN
THE WAY, I'M TELLIN' YA.

08:28.899 --> 08:30.510
-WELL, HE WANTS TO
INCLUDE OUR BOAT RESCUE

08:30.640 --> 08:32.294
IN HIS PILOT EPISODE. [CHUCKLES]

08:32.424 --> 08:33.337
AND HE'S SAID THAT SOME OF US

08:33.469 --> 08:35.253
MIGHT BE ABLE TO PLAY OURSELVES.

08:35.384 --> 08:38.429
-HELLO? THESE HOLLYWOOD-TYPES
WILL SAY ANYTHING TO GET A DEAL.

08:38.561 --> 08:40.432
-IT'S NOT SO FAR
FETCHED, YA KNOW.

08:41.956 --> 08:44.261
I STUDIED DRAMA IN COLLEGE.
-MITCH: OH.

08:44.393 --> 08:45.699
-I EVEN PLAYED MEDEA ONCE.

08:45.829 --> 08:48.789
-OH. SO YOU WANNA BE ON TV, NOW?

08:49.616 --> 08:51.182
-I DON'T KNOW.

08:51.313 --> 08:54.359
THE MORE I THINK ABOUT IT,
WHY NOT? WOULDN'T YOU?

08:54.490 --> 08:57.406
-NO WAY! 100 PERCENT, NO WAY!

09:03.717 --> 09:05.936
-SO WHO MAKE BETTER
LIFEGUARDS: MEN OR WOMEN?

09:06.067 --> 09:08.504
-UM, MEN, DEFINITELY. COME ON.

09:09.549 --> 09:12.029
MEN ARE BETTER IN EVERY
ASPECT OF THIS JOB.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.989
-WOMEN, DEFINITELY.
WE HAVE MUCH BETTER INSTINCTS

09:15.119 --> 09:18.122
'CAUSE WE CAN SOLVE
PROBLEMS BEFORE THEY HAPPEN.

09:19.297 --> 09:20.647
-NOW, MATT SAYS YOU'RE A COUPLE.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.300
DOES THAT MAKE IT
HARDER TO WORK TOGETHER?

09:23.301 --> 09:24.651
-YEAH, SOMETIMES.

09:24.781 --> 09:29.394
-HARDER? NEVER, NO.
IT NEVER GET IN THE WAY AT ALL.

09:30.265 --> 09:32.267
-THAT'S STRANGE.
SUMMER SAID IT DOES.

09:33.050 --> 09:35.357
-SHE DID?
-YEAH.

09:35.487 --> 09:38.360
THAT'S FUNNY.
MATT SAYS MEN MAKE BETTER
LIFEGUARDS THAN WOMEN.

09:39.970 --> 09:41.276
-HE DID?

09:46.890 --> 09:48.805
-HEY, LOOK. I'M
JUST HERE TO OBSERVE,

09:48.936 --> 09:50.415
JUST GO ON ABOUT YOUR BUSINESS.

09:50.546 --> 09:53.201
WE'LL CHECK UP BACK HERE,
WHATEVER YOU GOTTA DO.

09:53.331 --> 09:57.684
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT TO AFFECT
THINGS ANY WAY, SHAPE, OR FORM,
OKAY? HEY, I JUST WANNA--

09:58.510 --> 10:00.861
WOW, DRAMA. I LOVE IT.
BEAUTIFUL.

