11:54.888 --> 11:56.193
AS I DO ABOUT THE ACTION.

11:56.324 --> 11:58.500
I MEAN, PEOPLE ARE
NOT GONNA COME BACK

11:58.630 --> 11:59.893
AND WATCH RESCUE
BAY WEEK AFTER WEEK

12:00.023 --> 12:01.459
UNLESS THEY--
THEY LIKE THE PEOPLE.

12:01.590 --> 12:03.113
UNLESS THEY CAN
SHARE THEIR LIVES.

12:03.244 --> 12:06.334
-[CHUCKLES] NOTHING TO
DO WITH WOMEN IN BIKINIS?

12:06.464 --> 12:08.118
-WELL, HEY, DOESN'T HURT.

12:08.945 --> 12:10.904
BUT YOU KNOW, PEOPLE WILL
JUST NOT WATCH THIS SHOW

12:11.034 --> 12:13.602
UNLESS WE TELL REALLY
GOOD STORIES ABOUT
INTERESTING PEOPLE.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.648
YOU'RE INTERESTING, STEPHANIE.
TELL ME A GOOD STORY.

12:16.779 --> 12:18.650
TELL ME A PERSONAL STORY.

12:24.656 --> 12:26.354
-WELL, I PROBABLY SHOULDN'T
BE TELLING YOU THIS,

12:26.484 --> 12:29.661
BUT MITCH AND I DATED

12:29.792 --> 12:31.141
WHEN I FIRST STARTED
LIFEGUARDING HERE.

12:32.229 --> 12:35.711
AND THEN WE SPLIT UP.
WELL, ACTUALLY, I LEFT.

12:36.668 --> 12:40.455
SEE, I WAS MARRIED AT THE
TIME, BUT MITCH DIDN'T KNOW.

12:40.585 --> 12:41.891
WELL, ACTUALLY, I WAS SEPARATED.

12:44.198 --> 12:45.112
IS THIS BORING TO YOU?

12:45.242 --> 12:46.983
-OH, NO. PLEASE KEEP GOING.

12:51.640 --> 12:54.425
-SO I FINALLY GOT DIVORCED

12:54.556 --> 12:57.037
AND WHEN I CAME BACK
TO WORK AT BAYWATCH,

12:57.689 --> 12:59.822
IT WAS REALLY AWKWARD
BECAUSE I WAS MITCH'S BOSS.

13:01.302 --> 13:02.694
BUT NOW, EVERYTHING'S FINE.

13:03.870 --> 13:05.393
BUT IT WAS REALLY
DRAMATIC AT THE TIME.

13:05.523 --> 13:08.396
-OH, DRAMA. I LOVE DRAMA.

13:13.227 --> 13:15.185
-LOOK, COME ON, MITCH.

13:15.316 --> 13:16.970
-OH, NO, NO, NO.
-EVERYONE'S TOLD ME
ABOUT THEIR PERSONAL LIFE.

13:17.100 --> 13:18.493
WHY WON'T YOU?
-LOOK, LET'S GET
ONE THING STRAIGHT.

13:18.623 --> 13:20.974
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING
TO DO WITH THIS. GOT IT?

13:21.104 --> 13:23.019
-YEAH. OKAY. SO YOU EVER HAD AN
AFFAIR WITH A COLLEAGUE?

13:23.150 --> 13:24.151
-ARE YOU DEAF?

13:24.281 --> 13:26.066
-NO. I'M JUST PERSISTENT, MAN.

13:26.196 --> 13:27.894
LOOK, COME ON, MITCH. WE GOTTA
GET TOGETHER ON THIS THING.

13:28.024 --> 13:30.722
LIFE IS SHORT AND SO IS MY
SHOOTING SCHEDULE. [CHUCKLES]

13:30.853 --> 13:32.115
LOOK, I'M ONLY
GOING TO BE SHOOTING

13:32.246 --> 13:33.813
ON YOUR BEACH HERE FOR TWO DAYS.

13:33.943 --> 13:35.640
-YOU'RE FILMING AN
ENTIRE PILOT IN TWO DAYS?

13:35.771 --> 13:37.686
-NO. AN ENTIRE
PRESENTATION, YOU SEE?

13:37.817 --> 13:38.992
NETWORKS DON'T SPLURGE
ON PILOTS ANYMORE.

13:39.122 --> 13:40.515
IT'S JUST A LITTLE TEN MINUTES.

13:40.645 --> 13:41.559
YOU SLAP TOGETHER A
SCENE, SOME DIALOGUE,

13:41.690 --> 13:43.126
A MAIN TITLE, YOU KNOW.

13:43.257 --> 13:44.171
AND THEY EITHER PUT YOU
ON THE FALL SCHEDULE,

13:44.301 --> 13:45.389
OR POW, YOU'RE A GHOST.

13:45.999 --> 13:47.565
-BASED ON TEN MINUTES?

13:47.696 --> 13:49.437
-HEY. THIS IS GONNA BE

13:49.567 --> 13:51.004
THE BEST TEN MINUTES
THEY'VE EVER SEEN.

13:51.134 --> 13:52.701
SEE, LOOK. I GOT A
FEELING ABOUT YOU, MITCH.

13:52.832 --> 13:55.356
LOOK, WAIT, WAIT. I WANT
YOU TO PLAY MIKE TOWER.

13:55.486 --> 13:57.053
-WHO?

13:57.184 --> 13:58.359
-MIKE TOWER, THE CHARACTER
I'M BASING ON YOU.

13:58.489 --> 13:59.316
I WANT YOU TO PLAY HIM.

13:59.447 --> 14:00.361
-FORGET IT.

14:00.491 --> 14:02.015
-NO, WAIT! LOOK, MAN, C'MON!

14:02.145 --> 14:03.712
YOU COULD BE A BIG STAR!
YOU'VE GOT EVERYTHING.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.106
THE HAIR, THE EYES, THE
SEX APPEAL, THE HAIR.

14:06.236 --> 14:07.759
-THANKS, BUT NO THANKS.

14:07.890 --> 14:08.891
-LOOK, LOOK. WELL, HANG ON.

14:10.110 --> 14:11.981
I'M TELLING YOU, YOU
COULD DO THIS. TRUST ME.

14:12.112 --> 14:14.505
-TRUST? LOOK, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE IN HOLLYWOOD,

14:14.636 --> 14:16.812
BUT IN MY WORLD, TRUST
HAS GOTTA BE EARNED.

14:18.248 --> 14:19.771
-TRUST HAS GOTTA BE EARNED?

14:19.902 --> 14:21.164
I LIKE THAT LINE. THAT'S
PRETTY GOOD. WHAT IS IT?

14:21.295 --> 14:23.166
IN MY WORLD, TRUST IS--
IS WHAT? SAY IT AGAIN.

14:23.297 --> 14:25.647
-TRUST HAS GOT TO BE EARNED.
-[ENGINE STARTS]

14:25.777 --> 14:27.475
-TRUST HAS GOT TO
BE EARNED. SOLID.

14:27.605 --> 14:29.956
LOOK, IF YOU CHANGE YOU
MIND WE'RE CASTING TOMORROW--

14:30.086 --> 14:31.348
TOMORROW MORNING.

14:34.264 --> 14:37.789
-[ENERGETIC ROCK MUSIC]
-[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

14:40.531 --> 14:41.793
-YEAH, HERE.

14:41.924 --> 14:43.230
-LADY: THANKS.
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

14:43.360 --> 14:44.796
-LADY: THANKS.

14:46.537 --> 14:47.887
-HE'S COMING
RIGHT NOW. ASK HIM.

14:48.017 --> 14:49.062
-NO, YOU ASK HIM.
-MATT: ASK HIM.

14:49.192 --> 14:50.846
-MR. BRAND?
-YEAH?

14:50.977 --> 14:52.369
-WHO'S GONNA BE
PLAYING MATT AND ME?

14:52.500 --> 14:54.110
-OH, YOUR CHARACTERS
ARE ALREADY CAST.

14:54.241 --> 14:55.895
I'VE GOT ELAINE ELLIOT,
DAVID BATTLE,

14:56.025 --> 14:57.679
BIG DAY-TIME SOAP OPERA STARS.

14:57.809 --> 15:00.682
HUGE FOLLOWING AND THEY
BOTH HAVE NETWORK DEALS.

15:01.509 --> 15:02.945
-ISN'T HE THAT REAL
MUSCLE-BOUND GUY?

15:03.076 --> 15:04.686
-YEAH, BUT I MEAN,
HE'S KINDA SENSITIVE

15:04.816 --> 15:06.470
AND DID I MENTION HE
HAS A NETWORK DEAL?

15:06.601 --> 15:08.037
-WELL, WHAT IS SHE LIKE?

15:08.168 --> 15:09.517
-MM, I DUNNO.

15:09.647 --> 15:11.823
CUTE, PERKY, ATHLETIC,
AND A BIG NETWORK DEAL.

15:14.174 --> 15:16.263
-[BOTH] NETWORK DEALS? [SCOFFS]

15:20.876 --> 15:23.270
-GARNER: HEY, STEPHANIE.
